Discussion.S:
The CeLC subdivision in the present study corresponds 
    for the main portion to the lateral CLC of McDonald ('821, 
    with a rostro-caudal extent a little bit larger.

Thus, this pPB region could relay visceral information 
    from the medial NTS (Torvik, '56; Contreras et al., '82; 
    Kalia and Sullivan, '82; Norgren and Smith, '88; 
    Altshuler et al., '89) and chemoceptive information from the 
    area postrema (Gallo et al., '90; Adachi et al., '91) to 
    the CeL.
